<p><a href="Knight_Bachelor" title="Knight Bachelor">Sir</a> <b>Peter Reginald Frederick Hall</b>, <a href="Order_of_the_British_Empire" title="Order of the British Empire">CBE</a> (born 22 November 1930) is an English theatre and film director. Hall founded the <a href="Royal_Shakespeare_Company" title="Royal Shakespeare Company">Royal Shakespeare Company</a> (1960–68) and directed the <a href="Royal_National_Theatre" title="Royal National Theatre">National Theatre</a> (1973–88). He has also been prominent in defending public subsidy of the arts in Britain.</p>
